      • find_scalefac_x34

        private int find_scalefac_x34(float[] xr,
                              float[] xr34,
                              int xrPos,
                              float l3_xmin,
                              int bw,
                              int sf_min)
        the find_scalefac* routines calculate a quantization step size which would introduce as much noise as is allowed. The larger the step size the more quantization noise we'll get. The scalefactors are there to lower the global step size, allowing limited differences in quantization step sizes per band (shaping the noise).
